---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "JennAir Wall Oven Repair | Southern California | JJW, JMW Double, NOIR Obsidian Interior Service";
const description = "JennAir (Jenn-Air) wall oven repair across Southern California. JJW double wall ovens, JMW microwave-combo, JBS speed ovens. RISE and NOIR collections including Obsidian Interior matte-black cavity. F2E1/F6E1 error codes, control panel diagnostic, convection fan service. OEM W10821712, W11232121, W10855641. $89 diagnostic waived with repair. Call (424) 325-0520.";

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/jennair-oven-repair/#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, JennAir Wall Oven Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/jennair-oven-repair/",
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$$"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "JennAir Wall Oven Repair",
    "provider": { "@type": "LocalBusiness", "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "My JennAir double oven shows F2E1, is this the known defect?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Possibly. F2E1 indicates button stuck or control panel short circuit, and there's a documented pattern of control panel failures on JJW2, JJW3, JMW, and JMW3 model families with serial numbers beginning with D or F, the issue reached consumer attention through class action investigation. Cause: control panel components are heat and steam sensitive, and the panel's physical location above the oven cavity means heat and steam naturally rise to it. Symptoms: F2E1 displays, random beeping, unresponsive or phantom button presses, ovens won't start or shut down during cycles. Before ordering parts: unplug 15 minutes for electronics discharge, then retest. About 15% of F2E1 resolve on extended reset. If persistent: control panel replacement (OEM W11232121 or W10855641 on combo models) $585-$820. On 2-to-5-year-old JJW/JMW units with F2E1, we advise owners about the defect pattern so they know this may recur, repair is valid but unit may show same issue again in 18-36 months."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "F6E1 over-temp code, what does it mean?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "F6E1 is over-temperature safety shutdown on the heating cavity (upper main oven on double ovens). The control detected cavity temperature exceeding safe operating range and cut heating element power to prevent damage. Two root causes: (1) heating element relay stuck closed on the Appliance Manager board (OEM W10821712), elements receive continuous power even when control commands off, $485-$680 replacement; (2) temperature sensor drift causing control to misread cavity temp and continue heating, RTD sensor $145-$215. Diagnostic sequence: test heating element resistance first (rules in/out element short), then check sensor resistance against spec, then inspect relays on Appliance Manager. F6E1 is a safety code, don't force cycles by power cycling repeatedly. Continued operation with F6E1 active damages control electronics."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What's the difference between JJW and JMW wall ovens?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "JJW = standard wall ovens (single or double cavity, convection or convection with steam option). JMW = microwave-combo configurations (wall oven plus built-in microwave in a single unit, common space-saving choice in LA condos and smaller-footprint kitchens). JBS = speed ovens (microwave + convection hybrid single cavity, cooks faster than conventional but smaller than standard wall oven). Service differences: JMW combo models add microwave-specific service (magnetron, door switches, high-voltage diode) on top of wall oven service, $285-$485 for microwave-specific parts. JBS speed ovens share most of the JJW oven architecture plus compact microwave components. All three share the JennAir control panel architecture, which means the F2E1 control panel defect pattern affects JJW2/JJW3/JMW/JMW3 families together."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does NOIR Obsidian Interior need special service?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mostly no, same internal architecture as RISE Collection ovens, same heating elements, same convection fan, same control boards. The Obsidian Interior is a matte-black glass oven cavity (aesthetic feature unique to JennAir NOIR, visually emphasizes food against dark background). Two service-relevant differences: (1) cavity glass is specifically formulated for NOIR and not cross-compatible with RISE oven cavity parts, if the glass cavity wall is damaged (rare, requires impact) it's an NOIR-specific order; (2) cosmetic cleaning is different, standard oven cleaners can streak the matte finish, owners should use NOIR-approved cleaning products to maintain the aesthetic. For functional service (heating, control, convection), NOIR ovens service exactly the same as RISE."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does JennAir wall oven repair cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Typical JennAir wall oven repairs: bake element $245-$385, broil element $265-$385, convection ring element $285-$425, convection fan motor $285-$425, RTD temperature sensor $145-$215, thermal fuse $95-$155, Appliance Manager board (OEM W10821712) $485-$680, control panel (OEM W11232121 standard, W10855641 for JMW combo) $585-$820, door hinge pair (drop-down) $320-$460, door gasket $195-$285, inner door glass $285-$385, outer door glass $385-$580 (NOIR-specific on NOIR ovens), self-clean latch motor $225-$325, meat probe receptacle $95-$155, oven light bulb + installation $85-$135, LED module (NOIR) $185-$285, magnetron (JMW combo only) $285-$425, microwave door switch (JMW combo only) $95-$145. Labor and parts quoted before work starts."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">LA · Orange · Ventura · San Bernardino · Riverside Counties</p>
        <h1>JennAir Wall Oven Repair</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">Factory-trained service on JennAir (Jenn-Air) wall ovens, JJW double ovens, JMW microwave-combo, JBS speed ovens, single and double configurations. RISE and NOIR collections including Obsidian Interior matte-black cavity. F2E1 control panel defect diagnostic. F6E1 over-temp resolution. Post-warranty specialists for 3-to-12-year-old JennAir wall ovens across LA.</p>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn-primary">☎ {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn-outline">Book Online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-img-wrap">
        <div class="hero-img-placeholder">
          <p>JennAir Wall Oven Repair</p>
          <p>Across Southern California</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🏅</span> BHGS Licensed #A49573</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🛡</span> Fully Insured</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">⚡</span> Same Day Available</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">🔩</span> OEM Parts on Truck</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="trust-icon">💬</span> $89 Diagnostic, Waived With Repair</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── SERVICE CLARITY ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">What we do</p>
      <h2>We repair every JennAir wall oven configuration.</h2>
      <p>Standard wall ovens (JJW series, single and double cavity, convection or steam-convection). Microwave-combo wall ovens (JMW series, oven + built-in microwave in one unit, common in condo kitchens across our service area: Wilshire Corridor, Newport Beach high-rises, Long Beach towers, Marina del Rey waterfront). Speed ovens (JBS series, microwave + convection hybrid). 27-inch and 30-inch widths. Both RISE Collection (brushed stainless, commercial handles) and NOIR Collection (matte black stainless with Obsidian Interior option).</p>
      <p>We carry the common failure parts on every truck: bake elements, broil elements, convection ring elements, RTD temperature sensors, thermal fuses, door gaskets. For control panel and Appliance Manager board failures (OEM W10821712, W11232121, W10855641) we order within 24 hours given the known failure patterns on JJW2/JJW3/JMW families.</p>
      <p>We're not JennAir-authorized, that network dispatches in-warranty service; call 1-800-536-6247 for units under 1-year base coverage. We're post-warranty specialists: <strong>BHGS #A49573, BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410), BBB A+ since 2022</strong>. Our average JennAir wall oven call is 3-to-12 years old, NOIR or RISE, across Sherman Oaks, Brentwood, Beverly Hills, Studio City, Calabasas, and Pasadena on the LA side; Newport Coast, Newport Beach, and Tustin in OC; Westlake Village, Hidden Hills, and Thousand Oaks in Ventura; and Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula wine-country in the IE.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── MODELS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Models we service</p>
      <h2>JennAir wall oven model families</h2>

      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JJW3 Double Wall Ovens (Current)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JJW3430 · JJW3830 · JJW3830DS · JJW3430DP · JJW3830DP01</p>
          <p>Current-generation double wall ovens, 30" width. Two independent cavities with true European convection (fan + ring element) on both levels. NOIR Obsidian Interior option on current generation. OEM Appliance Manager board W10821712 on JJW3830 family. Most common premium JennAir double oven in luxury kitchens across our service area for 2015+.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JJW2 Double Wall Ovens (Earlier)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JJW2430 · JJW2830 · JJW2430DP01 · JJW2430WP02</p>
          <p>Earlier JJW2 generation, 2010-2016. Included in documented F2E1 control panel failure pattern (serial numbers beginning D or F). Most units reaching 10-14 year service territory now, control panel replacements becoming routine on this generation. Still serviceable, parts availability good.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JMW / JMW3 Microwave-Combo</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JMW2430 · JMW3430WS · JMW3430DP · JMW3430IM</p>
          <p>Oven-microwave combination units, wall oven below + built-in microwave above in single installation. Common in condos and townhomes across our service area (Westside LA, Newport Beach, Long Beach, Irvine apartments) where separate microwave space isn't available. OEM control panel W10855641 on JMW2430 family. Same F2E1 defect pattern affects JMW/JMW3 families due to shared control architecture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JJW Single Wall Ovens</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JJW2430 single · JJW2830 single · JJW3430 single</p>
          <p>Single cavity wall ovens, 27" or 30" width. Common in smaller-footprint kitchens or as supplemental oven alongside other cooking appliances. Same heating, convection, and control architecture as double oven variants (same parts, same diagnostics), just one cavity instead of two.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JBS Speed Ovens</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JBS7524 · JBS7524DS · JBS-speed variants</p>
          <p>Speed ovens, microwave + convection hybrid in single compact cavity. Cooks 2-3x faster than conventional oven with roasting browning quality. Specialty category in luxury kitchens across our service area (Westside LA, Newport Coast, Westlake Village, Rancho Cucamonga estates) where second oven space is prioritized but full-size secondary oven isn't warranted. Combined service profile: wall oven heating + microwave components (magnetron, door switches).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Legacy Wall Ovens (Pre-2012)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JJW9630AAW · JJW9627AAB · W246W · W256 · W266</p>
          <p>Pre-2012 legacy JennAir wall ovens. Still serviceable for common failures (heating elements, door hinges, sensors). Some electronic components may have reduced parts availability on 15+ year units. Honest repair-vs-replace assessment for pre-2010 units, most repairs still make sense if the underlying oven is structurally sound.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── F-CODE DECODER ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Error code decoder</p>
      <h2>JennAir wall oven F-codes</h2>
      <table class="price-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning &amp; diagnostic</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>F2E1</strong></td><td>Button stuck / control panel short. Documented defect pattern on JJW2/JJW3/JMW/JMW3 serial D or F. 15-min reset first (15% resolve). Control panel W11232121 or W10855641 $585-$820.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>F6E1</strong></td><td>Over-temp safety shutdown (upper cavity on double ovens). Appliance Manager W10821712 stuck relay $485-$680 OR RTD sensor drift $145-$215. Don't force cycles.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>F5</strong></td><td>Watchdog / hardware conflict, control board clock fault. Main control or clock board replacement $385-$580.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>F7</strong></td><td>Function key / touchpad fault. Random beeping, ghost button inputs. Usually ribbon cable aging or touchpad $425-$620.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>4d21 / 4d41</strong></td><td>Bake mode shutdown during cooking. Usually thermal-related: element overheating, thermal fuse about to trip, sensor drift. Full diagnostic needed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Display blank</strong></td><td>Not a code, user interface power failure. Check 5V at board (absent = main board $385-$580, present = touch panel $425-$620).</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><strong>Reset procedure:</strong> breaker off 10-15 min (electronics capacitors discharge), then restore. Clears transient codes. On JJW/JMW control panel issues related to F2E1 specifically, extended 15-min reset preferred because control capacitors hold longer.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMMON PROBLEMS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Common failures</p>
      <h2>The eight things that break on a JennAir wall oven</h2>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>1. F2E1, control panel defect (JJW/JMW families)</h3>
        <p>The #1 JennAir wall oven failure we see on 3-to-8-year-old units. Documented pattern on JJW2, JJW3, JMW, JMW3 families with serial numbers beginning D or F. Control panel components are heat and steam sensitive, and their location above the oven cavity means normal cooking heat and steam naturally rise to them. Failure accumulates over 2-5 years, symptoms progress from occasional phantom beeps to total unresponsiveness. Control panel replacement $585-$820 (OEM W11232121 standard, W10855641 for JMW combo). We advise owners: repair is valid but same failure may recur in 18-36 months given the design vulnerability, plan for this when deciding repair vs replacement on older units.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>2. F6E1, over-temp safety shutdown</h3>
        <p>Safety cutoff when control detects cavity over-temperature on upper main oven (double oven models) or single cavity (single models). Primary cause (70%): Appliance Manager board (OEM W10821712) has stuck heating element relay, elements receive continuous power even when control requests off, causing runaway temperature. Replacement $485-$680. Secondary cause (30%): RTD temperature sensor drift causing control to misread cavity temp, sensor $145-$215. Don't force cycles by power cycling repeatedly with F6E1 active; each cycle with the fault accumulates damage to other electronics.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>3. Heating element failure, mode-specific diagnostic</h3>
        <p>Regular bake doesn't heat but broil works: bake element failed ($245-$385). Broil doesn't work but bake does: broil element ($265-$385). Convection bake doesn't work but convection roast does: ring element ($285-$425, only in type-C convection cavities, most current JJW3 and JMW3 models have this architecture). Multimeter continuity test identifies which element at 20-50 ohms resistance; broken element reads open. All three elements replaceable from front cavity access.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>4. Convection fan motor failure</h3>
        <p>Symptoms: convection modes don't circulate air properly, uneven cooking, sometimes audible grinding or rattling during convection. Motor is located at rear of oven cavity accessed from back of unit. Built-in wall oven installation means the unit often must be pulled from its opening to access, adding labor. Motor replacement $285-$425 plus removal/reinstall labor. We assess access at your specific kitchen before quoting full cost.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>5. Oven temperature inaccurate, RTD drift or calibration</h3>
        <p>Oven runs 15-45°F off setpoint, baked goods don't brown properly, self-clean cycle aborts. Two causes. (1) Temperature Offset calibration uncalibrated, JennAir wall ovens have built-in calibration adjustment in Settings menu, free with any other repair or $95 standalone. (2) RTD temperature sensor drift, sensor reads wrong temp to control, $145-$215 replacement. We verify against cavity thermocouple measurement before ordering sensor.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>6. Door won't close properly, gasket or hinge</h3>
        <p>Wall oven doors weigh 28-55 lb depending on single/double and glass configuration. Hinges wear over 10-15 years. Symptoms: heat escaping around perimeter, slow preheat, energy waste. Hinge pair replacement $320-$460 (both for balanced operation). Gasket often needs simultaneous replacement if compressed unevenly $195-$285. On NOIR wall ovens, outer door glass is NOIR-specific (not interchangeable with RISE), $385-$580 if damaged.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>7. JMW combo microwave stops working (oven still works)</h3>
        <p>On JMW microwave-combo units, the microwave component can fail independently of the oven below. Diagnostic: door interlock switches ($95-$145 each, 2-3 switches in series for safety), magnetron tube ($285-$425, most common on 8+ year units), high-voltage diode ($65-$95), capacitor ($85-$145). Safety note: microwave service requires HV capacitor discharge before any work, this is not DIY. The oven portion continues functioning normally during microwave failure, so partial use is possible while waiting for service.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>8. Self-clean cycle won't complete</h3>
        <p>Multiple possible causes. Door latch motor failed (cycle can't lock for self-clean safety), $225-$325. Thermal fuse tripped (one-time safety fuse trips if cavity exceeds self-clean max temp), $95-$155 replacement PLUS identifying why it tripped (sensor drift, stuck element). Control board self-clean program fault, firmware update sometimes resolves on 2020+ Home Connect units ($85 flat), otherwise $385-$580 board. We diagnose before ordering parts, cheap fuse may be all that's needed vs expensive board.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── PRICING ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Pricing</p>
      <h2>What JennAir wall oven repair usually costs</h2>
      <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Labor and parts quoted separately before work starts.</p>
