  </section>

  <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>JennAir wall oven repair, common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F2E1 control panel, is this the known defect?</summary>
        <p>Yes, likely. Documented pattern on JJW2/JJW3/JMW/JMW3 serial D or F. 15-min reset first (15% resolve). Control panel replacement $585-$820. May recur in 18-36 months given design vulnerability.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F6E1 over-temp, what to do?</summary>
        <p>Safety shutdown. 70% Appliance Manager board stuck relay ($485-$680). 30% RTD sensor drift ($145-$215). Don't force cycles, accumulates electronic damage.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>JJW vs JMW vs JBS, different service?</summary>
        <p>JJW = standard wall ovens. JMW = oven+microwave combo (adds magnetron/door switches to diagnosis). JBS = speed oven hybrid. Core oven architecture shared across all three; combo models add microwave-specific parts.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>NOIR Obsidian Interior, special service?</summary>
        <p>Functional service identical to RISE. Only differences: cavity glass is NOIR-specific (not cross-compatible), and use NOIR-approved cleaners to preserve matte finish.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does JennAir wall oven repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common: bake element $245-$385, convection fan $285-$425, Appliance Manager board $485-$680, control panel $585-$820, hinge pair $320-$460. Full pricing above.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── BOTTOM CTA ── -->
  <section class="bottom-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to schedule JennAir wall oven service?</h2>
      <p>Same day available. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair. Temperature calibration included free with any repair.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
